ided an all-in-one facility for abused victims situated at the Quezon City General Hospital. Various services, namely, legal, medical, and psychiatric are freely provided for the victims, the QC Hall Breastfeeding Station, which aims to assist nursing mothers who are attending to matters in the City Hall<ref>{{cite web |title = BREASTFEEDING STATIONS NOW AVAILABLE AT THE QC CITY HALL|url=https://momcenter.com.ph/2014/12/07/breastfeeding-stations-now-available-at-the-qc-city-hall/ |accessdate=23 April 2019}}</ref> and the Values Formation for Parents, which intends to mold the attendees into responsible parents and members of the society\n\nShe has also instigated projects aimed at specific sectors such as women, children and senior citizens, namely the Maternal Health Care Project, Breastfeeding Advocacy Program, Breast Cancer Awareness and Examination Program, Cleft Lip/Palate Care Program, Nutri-Juice Feeding Program and the Zero Cataract Program\n\nOn July 27, 2017, Belmonte made headlines when she was in-charge as acting mayor during a monsoon because she refused to suspend classes early but still did when the students were stranded already. She predicted that  \"there would be only light rains\" based on a bulletin contrary to what happened. Belmonte said she acknowledges her \"shortcomings in this situation\", and stated that the residents \"'deserve a better leader\" because of the incident.<ref>{{cite web |title=Quezon City's Joy Belmonte under fire for initially not suspending classes |url=https://www.rappler.com/nation/176850-quezon-city-vice-mayor-joy-belmonte-under-fire-walang-pasok |accessdate=July 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn November 6, 2018 the \"Batas QC\" was launched, spearheaded by Belmonte. This initiative is the first mobile application in the Philippines to feature local ordinances. Its aim is to raise awareness regarding the rules and the corresponding penalties of non-compliance in order to minimize the violations among the people in the city.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1056852|title=Quezon City launched many 'firsts in PH' in 2018|last=Share|last2=Twitter|website=pna.gov.ph|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\nOn February 2019, Belmonte was accused of graft by [[Manuel Morato]], a former chairman of the [[Philippine Charity Sweepstakes Office]]. Belmonte denied the accusations and filed a libel case against 11 people including Morato.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/nation/2019/02/19/1894806/joy-belmonte-files-libel-case-vs-manuel-morato-tabloid-execs|title=Joy Belmonte files libel case vs Manuel Morato, tabloid execs|website=The Philippine Star|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/02/18/qc-vice-mayor-files-libel-charges-against-morato|title=QC vice mayor files libel charges against Morato|website=Manila Bulletin News|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>.\n\n===2019\u2013present: Mayor of Quezon City ===\nOn February 14, 2018, she announced that she intends to run for the mayoral position of Quezon City in the 2019 General Elections. She had agreed to run under the [[Hugpong ng Pagbabago]] with incumbent councilor & actor [[Gian Sotto]] as her running mate. <ref>{{Citation|last=ABS-CBN News|title=Headstart- QC mayoral candidate Joy Belmonte {{!}} ANC|date=2019-04-15|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X5PLqqbiyso|access-date=2019-04-23}}</ref>\n\nHer platform includes furthering women's rights, the addition of closed-circuit television cameras along the streets, upgrading the systems of documentation, and intensification of the anti-drug campaign.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/03/08/belmonte-reveals-pro-women-platform-of-governance-as-she-signs-covenant-with-fellow-leaders|title=Belmonte reveals pro-women platform of governance as she signs covenant with fellow leaders|website=Manila Bulletin News|access-date=2019-04-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-ph/news/national/joy-belmonte-shun-lies-black-propaganda/ar-BBVoDfM|title=Joy Belmonte: Shun lies, black propaganda|publisher=MSN|access-date=2019-04-23}}</ref> This platform was created with the help of 50 experts in multiple fields.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metromanila.politics.com.ph/2018/11/28/joy-belmonte-gets-50-experts-to-draft-mayoral-platform/|title=Joy Belmonte gets 50 experts to draft mayoral platform|date=2018-11-28|website=Politiko Metro Manila|access-date=2019-04-23}}</ref> Other more concrete points of her platform include child-minding centers; creating homes for abandoned senior citizens; a 24/7 emergency hotline; discounts for solo parents and PWDs.<ref name=\":4\" /> Joy has signed a covenant with women leaders of the Quezon City Community Women Leaders\u2019 Federation.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite news|url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/03/08/belmonte-reveals-pro-women-platform-of-governance-as-she-signs-covenant-with-fellow-leaders/|title=Belmonte reveals pro-women platform of governance as she signs covenant with fellow leaders|last=Chavez|first=Chito|date=March 8, 2019|work=Manila Bulletin}}</ref> This covenant assured that the points of the Quezon City Community Women Leaders\u2019 Federation ten-point agenda such as specialty clinic for women illnesses and mental health, and livelihood training center for the women entrepreneurs.<ref name=\":5\" />\n\nShe won against her closest rival, then-incumbent 1st District representative [[Vincent Crisologo]], in a large margin and was proclaimed the 11th Mayor of Quezon City.<ref>{{cite web |title=Joy Belmonte has massive lead over Crisologo in QC mayoral contest |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/05/13/19/joy-belmonte-ahead-in-quezon-city-after-polls-close |accessdate=May 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn her first months in office, she led the operations to clear out any road-blocking vehicles from highways within the city and asked for an extension of the 60-day deadline given by President [[Rodrigo Duterte]] to local executive chiefs to \"reclaim all public roads\". Belmonte said that Quezon City is \"too large\" for the mandate to be done within the required duration. By September 2019, she ordered to remove Senator [[Benigno Aquino, Jr.]]'s monument in [[Quezon Avenue]], dismantle stalls inside the [[Quezon City Memorial Circle]] and formed the \"Task Force 60 Days\" and the \"Solid-Waste Collection Task Force\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chavez |first1=Chito |title=City gov't starts dismantling stalls inside QC Memorial Circle |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2019/08/06/city-govt-starts-dismantling-stalls-inside-qc-memorial-circle/ |website=news.mb.com.ph |accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nJoy Belmonte is the wife of Raymond Alimurung, the first Filipino CEO of [[Lazada Group|Lazada]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/business/07/04/18/lazada-philippines-names-first-filipino-ceo|title=Lazada Philippines names first Filipino CEO|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref> They have a son named Gael.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metromanila.politics.com.ph/2018/11/27/joy-belmonte-preparing-husband-son-from-politiko-mudslinging/|title=Joy Belmonte preparing husband, son from politiko mudslinging|date=2018-11-27|website=Politiko Metro Manila|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2001 up until 2010, Joy served as the President of the Quezon City Ladies Foundation, Inc.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://quezoncitycouncil.ph/vicemayor.php|title=Quezon City Council - Sangguniang Panlungsod Lungsod Quezon {{!}} Ma. Josefina G. Belmonte|website=quezoncitycouncil.ph|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref> \n\nIn 2010, she was awarded the Gawad Lingkod Masa Award by [[Gabriela Women's Party]] due to her exceptional work on protecting and helping out distressed women.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://manilastandard.net/lgu/ncr/261930/gabriela-presents-joy-with-leadership-award.html|title=Gabriela presents Joy with leadership award|work=Manila Standard|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, she became an Ambassador of Peace for the [[Universal Peace Foundation]]. She also became a Paul Harris Fellow at the [[Rotary Foundation of Rotary International]].<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nOn July 12, 2017, Belmonte accepted her appointment as part of the new [[Metro Manila Film Festival]] executive committee. <ref>[http://www.interaksyon.com/entertainment/2017/07/12/84367/maryo-j-delos-reyes-arnell-ignacio-joy-belmonte-named-new-mmff-execom-members/]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Mayors of Quezon City}}\n{{Mayors of Metro Manila}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Belmonte, Joy}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Quezon City]]\n[[Category:Quezon City Council members]]\n[[Category:Filipino Christians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of University College London]]\n[[Category:Ateneo de Manila University alumni]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Leicester]]\n", "name_user": "112.205.190.186", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joy_Belmonte"}
